        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14919",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ledezma",
                        "name": "ledezma",
                        "displayName": "Salvador Ledezma",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "unit tests added for automatic quoting property",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ledezma",
                        "name": "ledezma",
                        "displayName": "Salvador Ledezma",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-06-01T19:10:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-06-01T19:10:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14920",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ledezma",
                        "name": "ledezma",
                        "displayName": "Salvador Ledezma",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please review the new property defined in the Zend_Db component.   At object construction, the property is set.  If true, all identifiers are automatically quoted.  If false, they are not.  The default is true.\n\nmost changes are made here in the abstract class.  The API quoteIdentifierAutomatically() is defined here.\nEvery call to quoteIdentifier() calls this new API.  If the call is made internally, a check of the property _alwaysQuoteIdentifiers is done.  if true, the identifier is quoted, otherwise it is left alone.  Some other methods had some api changes made as well to support the new API.\nAn external call to quoteIdentifier() behaves as previously, the identifier is quoted.\nFiles changed include\nlib\/Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/Abstract.php\nlib\/Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/Db2.php\n\nconstant ALWAYS_QUOTE_IDENTIFIERS is defined here\nZend\/Db.php\n\nnew API had to be called here\nlib\/Zend\/Db\/Select.php\nlib\/Zend\/Db\/Table\/Abstract.php\nlib\/Zend\/Db\/Table\/Row\/Abstract.php\n\nunit tests added (at the end of the file).  These show how the configuration property can be used.  There are no other changes to external APIs.\ntests\/Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/TestCommon.php\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ledezma",
                        "name": "ledezma",
                        "displayName": "Salvador Ledezma",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-06-01T19:16:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-06-01T19:16:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14942",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks very much for the patch and doing the work, Salvador.  I have updated it a little bit and I committed it with support and tests for all the Zend_Db adapters.\n\nI made the following functional changes relative to your patch:\n- Zend_Db::AUTO_QUOTE_IDENTIFIERS is the name of the const naming the option\n- No need to make a new function {{quoteIdentifierAutomatically()}}.  Instead, I added an optional param to the usual {{quoteIdentifier()}} method.  If the second parameter is {{true}}, the method uses the current setting of the autoQuoteIdentifer config.  Otherwise the parameter defaults to {{false}} and it means to explicitly return a quoted identifier.\n- Restructured unit tests to utilize the adapter's TestUtil class.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-06-04T14:08:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-06-04T14:08:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14943",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Implementation, tests, and docs committed in revision 5100.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-06-04T14:08:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-06-04T14:08:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19268",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mben",
                        "name": "mben",
                        "displayName": "Marc Bennewitz (GIATA mbH)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I need support to deactivate auto qoting if the configuration option Zend_Db::AUTO_QUOTE_IDENTIFIERS is set to true.\n\n{code}\n\/\/ current\n$mysql->quoteIdentifier('my.table.as.column');   \/\/ `my`.`table`.`as`.`column`\n$mysql->quoteIdentifier('my.table.as.column', true);   \/\/ `my`.`table`.`as`.`column`\n$mysql->quoteIdentifier('my.table.as.column', false);   \/\/ `my`.`table`.`as`.`column`\n\n\/\/ need\n$mysql->quoteIdentifier('my.table.as.column');   \/\/ `my`.`table`.`as`.`column`\n$mysql->quoteIdentifier('my.table.as.column', true);   \/\/ `my`.`table`.`as`.`column`\n$mysql->quoteIdentifier('my.table.as.column', false);   \/\/ `my.table.as.column`\n{code}\n\nset the default value of the second argment in quoteIdentifier to NULL\nif $auto === null then use Zend_Db::AUTO_QUOTE_IDENTIFIERS\nelse use the $auto",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mben",
                        "name": "mben",
                        "displayName": "Marc Bennewitz (GIATA mbH)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-19T17:14:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-19T17:14:05.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
